TRAINERS METHODOLOGY - D19

CONDUCT COMPETENCY ASSESSMENT

Steps in conducting assessment:
-Establish the context and purpose of assessment
-Plan and prepare evidence-gathering process
-Prepare the candidate
-Collect the evidence and ake the assessment decision
-Provide feedback on the assessment


Establish the context and purpose of assessment
The assessor must:
>Familiarize self with the Qualification and Units of Competency to be assessed
>Ensure that the assessment site complies with the relevant Occupational Health Standard requirements
>Ensure that assessment resources are available
>Complete set of safe and functional equipment and tools
>Complete set of supplies and materials
>Personal Proective Equipment
>Assessor's Guide and Rating Sheets


Plan and prepare evidence-gathering process
The assessor shall:
-Check and receive Assessment Package composed of the following from the TESDA Representative:
>Appointment LEtter
>Assessor's Guide
>Rating Sheets
>Competency Assessment REsults Summary (CARS)
>Specific Instructions to the Candidate


Prepare the candidate
The assessor shall:
-Check attendance and identity of the candidates and collect admission slips
-Instruct the candidates to sign on the Attendance Sheet
-Conduct Orientation on candidates
  >Purpose: to check candidate's readiness for assessment
  >Qualification for assessment
  >Assessment and certification arrangement


